<Content>Great place, great people My husband and I stayed at this delightful small hotel on a few occasions e and look forward to our next stay. We were assigned different rooms varying in size, but all turned out to be more than adequate. The hotel is very clean and immaculately kept. All of the high class hotel equipment is available, such as internet PC in your room, bathroom phone line, hair dryer and so on. The staff has always shown a genuine wish to help out with all sorts of requests, from travel arrangements, to restaurant reservations and shopping advise. Frank, one of the receptionists also runs splendid private walking tours of the history and art of Florence which we thoroughly enjoyed and would recommend taking. Breakfast is good, but only continental, no cooked food (by the way, breakfast may be worth only just to be served tea and coffee in their wonderful genuine antique silverware). What we always found extraordinary of this place is the atmosphere, of a quiet and relaxed 19th century Tuscan home where you are filled with attention from fresh flowers in you room, chocolates by your bed at turndown, a concierge with a smile at your arrival and many politeness impossible to enjoy in larger, commercial establishments. We once found in our room invitations to a concert at the nearby famous Teatro della Pergola, compliments of the hotel manager. The location is very good indeed, we could walk to all we are interested in and, though in the centre of the city, in a very quiet location. We did try other more expensive hotels before, but this is definitely our first choice in Florence and have recommended to friends who returned sharing our impression. 
