<Content>Great place in Florence, do your own parking! We stayed at Morandi Alla Crocetta for one night in Sept. 2004. The hotel is close to the Duomo but is hard to find on a small one way street in an area of many one way streets. We had to keep circling in our rental car. Once there the hotel is up one level from the street without lift. Reception helped with bags. I chose this hotel because reviews were good, close in, and parking available. Street is narrow at their one bay parking garage. The clerk offered to park the car because of the tight fit however, in the course of him trying to park it he ran it into the garage door jamb on the right rear fender and then the rear bumper on the left side. Luckly I had insurance! The staff was very professional, proper, nice and helpfull. The double room had an extra bed and a couch. It was tight but nicely furnished with antiques and romantic. Bed was comfortable, bath with small shower, very clean. Free in room internet was nice. Don't go for the appearance from the street or the fact that it was a convent, you can't tell it. Did't take the 11 Euro breakfast, did not see it to tell if it would be worth it either. Great snack bar for breakfast and lunch at end of street on the right corner towards Duomo. We had a great stay and would go back but we will do our own parking! 
