<Content>perfect quiet spot in Florence We stayed for four nights in mid-September. While the front was a bit off-setting, the rooms were perfect. We had two rooms (doubles) that could have actually slept three. Each room had a nice sitting area and very nice sized bathrooms. After our first day of sightseeing, the hotel provided a computer with internet services (without our request) which came in quite handy to make train reservations. The hotel is nicely situated near the Duomo and Accademia, both areas with nice restaurants and within easy walking distance. The staff was very friendly and accomodating. I will be staying here again upon returning to Florence. 
