<Author>Teresuzza
<Content>Great Atmosphere This hotel provided a great, relaxing atmosphere after days of sightseeing and touring around. The front desk staff is very attentive and very well mannered. They only have one spot in their parking garage and we were lucky enough to get it. They charge 16 euros a day for it, but, well worth it. The location is close to the Duomo and within walking distance of all of Florence's attractions. The only drawback is that this hotel is on the second floor and has no elevator. With four of us travelling, 2 adults and 2 teenagers, hauling the luggage up the stairs was quite the task. However, upon arrival and check-in, the front desk person helped with all the baggage....truly amazing! The room was quite nice...a little small..but nice! Breakfast is outrageously priced at 11 euros per person so we skipped that and enjoyed the cafes on the streets nearby. I agree with the previous review that the hotel has an 'old' smell to it, but not unbearable or irritating in any way. It just adds to the atmosphere of this place. 
